Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil. Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 400 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Zest ½ tsp zest from @lemon{1}, then quarter. Squeeze 1 TBSP juice into a #small bowl (save any remaining lemon for another use). Cut @Roma tomato{4} into ½-inch-thick wedges.

Line a #baking sheet{} with #aluminum foil{}, then arrange tomato wedges on it skin sides down. Drizzle with @olive oil{1%tsp}; season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tsp} (save the rest for step 4). Roast on top rack until wilted and beginning to release their juices, about ~{25%minutes}.

Once tomatoes have roasted ~{10%minutes}, add @spaghetti{12%oz} to pot of boiling water. Cook until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain. Set spaghetti aside in #strainer; keep pot handy for use in step 5.

Pat @chicken breast strips{20%oz} dry with #paper towels and season with salt, pepper, and remaining @Tuscan Heat Spice{3%tsp}. Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a large #pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from heat.

Add @butter{2%tbsp} to pot used for pasta and place over medium-low heat. Add lemon zest, @cream cheese{6%tbsp}, and ¾ cup pasta cooking water and whisk until smooth. Stir in spaghetti, @garlic herb butter{2%tbsp}, reserved lemon juice, and half the @Parmesan cheese{¾%cup}. (TIP: If pasta seems dry, add more cooking water, a little at a time, until coated in a loose sauce.) Toss in chicken, then season with salt and pepper.

Pick @basil{½%oz} leaves from stems; discard stems and roughly chop or tear leaves. Divide pasta between #bowls and top with tomatoes. Garnish with basil and remaining Parmesan.